        <p>ScDNA-seq data display tumor heterogeneity. (<bold>A</bold>) Joint tumor phylogeny tree by SNV and CNA, where the gray node represents normal cells and the other nodes are cancerous cells. The letters A, B, and C are mutation loci. The bars under each letter represent alleles, and the bars with red stars and triangles are mutated. (<bold>B</bold>) The SNV genotype matrix, <inline-formula><tex-math notation="LaTeX" id="ImEquation14">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
