\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}$^2$\end{document}</tex-math></inline-formula></italic> takes the observed total reads and mutant reads at multiple loci in single cells as input and assigns cells to subclones. By applying MCMC sampling, <italic toggle="yes">BiTSC<inline-formula><tex-math notation="LaTeX" id="ImEquation18">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
